{"lemma":"رَبابٌ","slug":"رَبابٌ","root":"ر.ب.ب","root_slug":"ر-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14376","n14377","n14378"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رُبّ (rubb)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَبَّ (rabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14376","headword_ar":"رَبَابٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds that one sees beneath other clouds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds suspended beneath other clouds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes white and sometimes black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) this latter is said by IB to be the signification commonly known: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds consisting of an accumulation of parts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, T:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A 'Obeyd, S, K.) Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~abaAbu","text_ar":"الرَّبَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a proper name of a woman. (A 'Obeyd, T, S.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain instrument of diversion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of music,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having strings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one plays"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbAb","text_ar":"رباب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in common use among the Arabs in the present day is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of viol."},{"kind":"text","text":"A specimen of it is figured and described in my work on the Modern Egyptians. Being an instrument of remarkable simplicity, it is probably similar to the ancient"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbAb","text_ar":"رباب"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Memdood Ibn-'Abd-Allah El-Wásitee Er-Rabábee became proverbial for his musical skill with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbAb","text_ar":"رباب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aAnN","text_ar":"رُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n14377","headword_ar":"رُبَابٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is an anomalous pl.:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aAnN","text_ar":"رُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14378","headword_ar":"رِبَابٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbapN","text_ar":"رِبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tithes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenths;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$uwrN","text_ar":"عُشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) from the same word signifying “ a covenant. ” (S.) ―         -b3-  In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuEoTiyhaA AlA^amaAna ribaAbuhaA","text_ar":"يُعْطِيهَا الاَمَانَ رِبَابُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", ending a verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb, describing some asses,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAb","text_ar":"رِبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An oath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a promise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which the owner of the asses takes of a people to permit those asses to water: or the poet means that the person giving those asses permission to water gives to their owner"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of those used in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as a token,] to show that they have received permission to water, and that no one may offer them any opposition: (TA:) some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAbuhaA","text_ar":"رِبَابُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"here means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their owners:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) [holding this last opinion,] Sh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAb","text_ar":"رِبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this verse is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~N","text_ar":"رَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  It is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~apN","text_ar":"رُبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) not of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rib~apN","text_ar":"رِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is said to be by Th [and in the K]. (M.)       -A3-  See also 1, last sentence.       -A4-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aAnN","text_ar":"رُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}